  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pulse induced continuous cardiac output (PiCCO) is an established technology for measurement
      of advanced hemodynamic variables in critically ill patients. PiCCO is approved and designed
      also for use in children, but there is a lack of documentation of reference values in
      children not suffering from a critical illness. The goal of this study is to establish such
      values.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
